    "id": "ml7z5b5n",
    "questionNumber": 4,
    "questionText": "<p>A Wheatstone bridge is initially at room temperature and all arms of the bridge have same value of resistances ($R_1 = R_2 = R_3 = R_4$). When $R_3$ resistance is heated to some temperature, its resistance value has gone up by 10%. The potential difference ($V_a - V_b$) (after $R_3$ is heated) is _________ V.</p><img alt=\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 28th January Evening Shift Physics - Current Electricity Question 24 English\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mlcamo3q/73bbc5e1-c6e9-4d2e-8b2a-7e48322a5bcd/ec0f8260-0420-11f1-b905-e3cf04b12e1d/file-6y3zli1mlcamo3r.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1mlcamo3q/73bbc5e1-c6e9-4d2e-8b2a-7e48322a5bcd/ec0f8260-0420-11f1-b905-e3cf04b12e1d/file-6y3zli1mlcamo3r.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\">",
    "options": [
      "<p>1.05</p>",
      "<p>0.95</p>",
      "<p>0</p>",
      "<p>2</p>"
    ],
    "correctOption": 1,
    "correctAnswer": null,
    "questionType": "MCQ",
    "marks": 4,
    "negativeMarks": -1,
    "subject": "Physics",
    "topic": "wheatstone-bridge",
    "difficulty": "medium",
    "solution": "<p>Initially : $\\mathrm{R}_1=\\mathrm{R}_2=\\mathrm{R}_3=\\mathrm{R}_4=\\mathrm{R}$.</p>\n<p>After heating $\\mathrm{R}_3$ :</p>\n<ul>\n\n<li><p>1. $\\mathrm{R}_1=\\mathrm{R}$</p></li>\n\n<li><p>2. $\\mathrm{R}_2=\\mathrm{R}$</p></li>\n\n<li><p>3. $\\mathrm{R}_3=\\mathrm{R}+10 \\%$ of $\\mathrm{R}=1.1 \\mathrm{R}$</p></li>\n\n<li><p>4. $\\mathrm{R}_4=\\mathrm{R}$</p></li>\n\n</ul>\n<p>Supply voltage $\\mathrm{V}=40 \\mathrm{~V}$.</p>\n<p><img alt=\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 28th January Evening Shift Physics - Current Electricity Question 24 English Explanation\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mlcapmoa/87705f70-b9dc-40f4-830e-278e618550c7/3e6256a0-0421-11f1-b905-e3cf04b12e1d/file-6y3zli1mlcapmob.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1mlcapmoa/87705f70-b9dc-40f4-830e-278e618550c7/3e6256a0-0421-11f1-b905-e3cf04b12e1d/file-6y3zli1mlcapmob.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p>\n<p>The voltage across $R_1$ and $R_2$ is 40 V . So the current in this branch is $i_a=\\frac{40 \\mathrm{~V}}{R_1+R_2}$.</p>\n<p>The voltage across $\\mathrm{R}_1=\\mathrm{V}_1=\\mathrm{i}_{\\mathrm{a}} \\mathrm{R}_1=\\left(\\frac{40 \\mathrm{~V}}{\\mathrm{R}_1+\\mathrm{R}_2}\\right) \\mathrm{R}_1=\\left(\\frac{40 \\mathrm{~V}}{\\mathrm{R}+\\mathrm{R}}\\right) \\mathrm{R}=20 \\mathrm{~V}$</p>\n<p>The voltage across $\\mathrm{R}_2=\\mathrm{V}_2=\\mathrm{i}_{\\mathrm{a}} \\mathrm{R}_2=\\left(\\frac{40 \\mathrm{~V}}{\\mathrm{R}_1+\\mathrm{R}_2}\\right) \\mathrm{R}_2=\\left(\\frac{40 \\mathrm{~V}}{\\mathrm{R}+\\mathrm{R}}\\right) \\mathrm{R}=20 \\mathrm{~V}$</p>\n<p>Assuming the potential of negative terminal of battery as 0 V then $\\mathrm{v}_{\\mathrm{a}}=\\mathrm{V}_2=20 \\mathrm{~V}$</p>\n<p>Similarly for the branch containing $\\mathrm{R}_3$ and $\\mathrm{R}_4$,</p>\n<p>The voltage across $R_3$ and $R_4$ is 40 V . So the current in this branch is $i_b=\\frac{40 \\mathrm{~V}}{R_3+R_4}$.</p>\n<p>The voltage across $R_3=V_3=i_b R_3=\\left(\\frac{40 \\mathrm{~V}}{R_3+R_4}\\right) R_3=\\left(\\frac{40 \\mathrm{~V}}{1.1 R+R}\\right)(1.1 R)=20.95 \\mathrm{~V}$</p>\n<p>The voltage across $\\mathrm{R}_4=\\mathrm{V}_4=\\mathrm{i}_{\\mathrm{b}} \\mathrm{R}_4=\\left(\\frac{40 \\mathrm{~V}}{\\mathrm{R}_3+\\mathrm{R}_4}\\right) \\mathrm{R}_4=\\left(\\frac{40 \\mathrm{~V}}{1.1 \\mathrm{R}+\\mathrm{R}}\\right) \\mathrm{R}=19.05 \\mathrm{~V}$</p>\n<p>Assuming the potential of negative terminal of battery as 0 V then $\\mathrm{v}_{\\mathrm{b}}=\\mathrm{V}_4=19.05 \\mathrm{~V}$</p>\n<p>So, the potential difference between points a and b is,</p>\n<p>$$ \\left(\\mathrm{V}_{\\mathrm{a}}-\\mathrm{V}_{\\mathrm{b}}\\right)=20 \\mathrm{~V}-19.05 \\mathrm{~V}=0.95 \\mathrm{~V} $$</p>\n<p>Therefore, the potential difference is 0.95 V . Hence, the correct option is (B).</p>",
    "section": "A",
    "type": "SCQ"
  },
  {
    "id": "m6rkxflx",
    "questionNumber": 21,
    "questionText": "<p>The value of current I in the electrical circuit as given below, when potential at A is equal to the potential at B, will be _______ A.</p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m6rkvf4e/ac2f0803-fcf9-4128-979a-54a90144108c/7dc106e0-e391-11ef-bd37-5bfdd6d633f7/file-jaoe38c1m6rkvf4f.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m6rkvf4e/ac2f0803-fcf9-4128-979a-54a90144108c/7dc106e0-e391-11ef-bd37-5bfdd6d633f7/file-jaoe38c1m6rkvf4f.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"JEE Main 2025 (Online) 28th January Evening Shift Physics - Current Electricity Question 44 English\">",
    "options": [],
    "correctOption": 0,
    "correctAnswer": null,
    "questionType": "NUMERICAL",
    "marks": 4,
    "negativeMarks": -1,
    "subject": "Physics",
    "topic": "wheatstone-bridge",
    "difficulty": "easy",
    "solution": "<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m74rxah0/24b431f2-9371-4201-9e48-bc2dde8abc76/42208040-ead3-11ef-955f-5dd397bbe371/file-jaoe38c1m74rxah1.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m74rxah0/24b431f2-9371-4201-9e48-bc2dde8abc76/42208040-ead3-11ef-955f-5dd397bbe371/file-jaoe38c1m74rxah1.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"JEE Main 2025 (Online) 28th January Evening Shift Physics - Current Electricity Question 44 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>$$\\begin{aligned}\n&amp; \\mathrm{V}_{\\mathrm{A}}=\\mathrm{V}_{\\mathrm{B}} \\Rightarrow \\text { the bridge is balanced } \\\\\n&amp; \\Rightarrow \\frac{10}{\\mathrm{R}}=\\frac{20}{40} \\\\\n&amp; \\mathrm{R}=20 \\Omega \\\\\n&amp; \\mathrm{I}=\\frac{40}{20}=2 \\mathrm{~A}\n\\end{aligned}$$</p>",
    "section": "B",
    "type": "NUMERICAL"
  },
  {
    "id": "m9e5j81w",
    "questionNumber": 5,
    "questionText": "<p>A wire of resistance $R$ is bent into a triangular pyramid as shown in figure with each segment having same length. The resistance between points $A$ and $B$ is $R / n$. The value of $n$ is :</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m9giznc5/85aa8347-4bfa-4650-a82e-0533aa355f6a/28125150-18e2-11f0-a103-9bd1ffe79f48/file-jaoe38c1m9giznc6.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m9giznc5/85aa8347-4bfa-4650-a82e-0533aa355f6a/28125150-18e2-11f0-a103-9bd1ffe79f48/file-jaoe38c1m9giznc6.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"JEE Main 2025 (Online) 7th April Morning Shift Physics - Current Electricity Question 36 English\"></p>",
    "options": [
      "16",
      "10",
      "12",
      "14"
    ],
    "correctOption": 2,
    "correctAnswer": null,
    "questionType": "MCQ",
    "marks": 4,
    "negativeMarks": -1,
    "subject": "Physics",
    "topic": "wheatstone-bridge",
    "difficulty": "medium",
    "solution": "<p>As $r=\\frac{R}{6}$</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m9l5wn8l/67f605f4-47b0-4f11-94d1-7d9014c93fec/e922cd50-1b6e-11f0-bbff-0f04539847fe/file-jaoe38c1m9l5wn8m.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m9l5wn8l/67f605f4-47b0-4f11-94d1-7d9014c93fec/e922cd50-1b6e-11f0-bbff-0f04539847fe/file-jaoe38c1m9l5wn8m.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"JEE Main 2025 (Online) 7th April Morning Shift Physics - Current Electricity Question 36 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>(As balanced wheat stone bridge is formed) Now, Equivalent resistance between A and B can be written as</p>\n<p>$$\\begin{aligned}\n&amp; \\frac{1}{\\mathrm{R}_{\\mathrm{AB}}}=\\frac{1}{2 \\mathrm{r}}+\\frac{1}{2 \\mathrm{r}}+\\frac{1}{\\mathrm{r}}=\\frac{2}{\\mathrm{r}} \\\\\n&amp; \\mathrm{R}_{\\mathrm{AB}}=\\frac{\\mathrm{R}}{12}\n\\end{aligned}$$</p>",
    "section": "A",
    "type": "SCQ"
  },
  {
    "id": "jaoe38c1lsc3vcj8",
    "questionNumber": 5,
    "questionText": "<p>A wire of length $$10 \\mathrm{~cm}$$ and radius $$\\sqrt{7} \\times 10^{-4} \\mathrm{~m}$$ connected across the right gap of a meter bridge. When a resistance of $$4.5 \\Omega$$ is connected on the left gap by using a resistance box, the balance length is found to be at $$60 \\mathrm{~cm}$$ from the left end. If the resistivity of the wire is $$\\mathrm{R} \\times 10^{-7} \\Omega \\mathrm{m}$$, then value of $$\\mathrm{R}$$ is :</p>",
    "options": [
      "63",
      "70",
      "66",
      "35"
    ],
    "correctOption": 2,
    "correctAnswer": null,
    "questionType": "MCQ",
    "marks": 4,
    "negativeMarks": -1,
    "subject": "Physics",
    "topic": "wheatstone-bridge",
    "difficulty": "medium",
    "solution": "<p>For null point,</p>\n<p>$$\\begin{aligned}\n& \\frac{4.5}{60}=\\frac{R}{40} \\\\\n& \\text { Also, } R=\\frac{\\rho \\ell}{A}=\\frac{\\rho \\ell}{\\pi r^2} \\\\\n& 4.5 \\times 40=\\rho \\times \\frac{0.1}{\\pi \\times 7 \\times 10^{-8}} \\times 60 \\\\\n& \\rho=66 \\times 10^{-7} \\Omega \\times \\mathrm{m}\n\\end{aligned}$$</p>",
    "section": "A",
    "type": "SCQ"
  },
  {
    "id": "lvc58eq8",
    "questionNumber": 3,
    "questionText": "<p>The value of unknown resistance $$(x)$$ for which the potential difference between $$B$$ and $$D$$ will be zero in the arrangement shown, is :</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lvbx7z99/54f999c0-8118-4029-b7cf-03308249cec2/dd0265e0-012e-11ef-b9e7-612d1e30f27e/file-1lvbx7z9a.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lvbx7z99/54f999c0-8118-4029-b7cf-03308249cec2/dd0265e0-012e-11ef-b9e7-612d1e30f27e/file-1lvbx7z9a.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"JEE Main 2024 (Online) 6th April Morning Shift Physics - Current Electricity Question 48 English\"></p>",
    "options": [
