    "difficulty": "medium",
    "solution": "<p>Equivalent circuit can be drawn as</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1leoi54ri/6dbd00fd-9061-4abc-9be2-5e05f3252362/67e627e0-b78a-11ed-8877-d5d81ac5ff88/file-1leoi54rj.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1leoi54ri/6dbd00fd-9061-4abc-9be2-5e05f3252362/67e627e0-b78a-11ed-8877-d5d81ac5ff88/file-1leoi54rj.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2023 (Online) 30th January Evening Shift Physics - Current Electricity Question 135 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>$$\\therefore$$ $$\\frac{1}{R_{AB}}=\\frac{7}{12}+\\frac{1}{4}+\\frac{2}{3}$$</p>\n<p>$$R_{AB}=\\frac{2}{3}~\\Omega$$</p>",
