  {
    "id": "tAQRGQNA5mwMliB8Ea1kmkbb9ft",
    "questionNumber": 6,
    "questionText": "The four arms of a Wheatstone bridge have resistances as shown in the figure. A galvanometer of 15$$\\Omega$$ resistance is connected across BD. Calculate the current through the galvanometer when a potential difference of 10V is maintained across AC.<br><br><img src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kmlicrx2/93df8086-5353-4443-bf23-ee443aaaa5d6/d3e43f60-8b8e-11eb-8bc4-81bde7104d98/file-1kmlicrx3.jpg\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"JEE Main 2021 (Online) 17th March Evening Shift Physics - Current Electricity Question 229 English\">",
    "options": [
      "4.87 $$\\mu$$A",
      "4.87 mA",
      "2.44 mA",
      "2.44 $$\\mu$$A"
    ],
    "correctOption": 1,
    "correctAnswer": null,
    "questionType": "MCQ",
    "marks": 4,
    "negativeMarks": -1,
    "subject": "Physics",
    "topic": "wheatstone-bridge",
    "difficulty": "medium",
    "solution": "$${{{V_B} - 10} \\over {100}} + {{{V_B} - {V_D}} \\over {15}} + {{{V_B} - 0} \\over {10}} = 10$$<br><br>$${{{V_B} - 10} \\over {20}} + {{{V_B} - {V_D}} \\over 3} + {{{V_B}} \\over 2} = 0$$<br><br>$$3{V_B} - 30 + 20{V_B} - 20{V_D} + 30{V_B} = 0$$<br><br>$$53{V_B} - 20{V_D} = 30$$ __________ (1)<br><br>Similarly,<br><br>$${{{V_D} - 10} \\over {60}} + {{{V_D} - {V_B}} \\over {15}} + {{{V_D} - 0} \\over 5} = 0$$<br><br>$${V_D} - 10 + 4{V_D} - 4{V_B} + 12{V_D} = 0$$<br><br>$$ - 4{V_B} + 17{V_D} = 10$$ __________ (2)<br><br>after solving equation (1) &amp; (2)<br><br>V<sub>D</sub> = 0.79 volt<br><br>V<sub>B</sub> = 0.86 volt<br><br>Then the current through the galvanometer<br><br>$$ = {{{V_B} - {V_D}} \\over R}$$<br><br>$$ = {{0.86 - 0.79} \\over {15}}$$ = 4.87 mA",
    "section": "A",
    "type": "SCQ"
  },
  {
    "id": "dSbAQiKANGGcftImN01kltjhz5q",
    "questionNumber": 6,
    "questionText": "Five equal resistances are connected in a network as shown in figure. The net resistance between the points A and B is :<br><br><img src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kltqoqnb/d4212562-3048-4e6b-8ff2-3f2144e5dd4d/77781f70-7c49-11eb-98b4-b931446ae6e4/file-1kltqoqnc-214w.jpg\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"JEE Main 2021 (Online) 26th February Morning Shift Physics - Current Electricity Question 238 English\">",
    "options": [
      "$${{3R} \\over 2}$$",
      "$${{R} \\over 2}$$",
      "2R",
      "R"
    ],
    "correctOption": 3,
    "correctAnswer": null,
    "questionType": "MCQ",
    "marks": 4,
    "negativeMarks": -1,
    "subject": "Physics",
    "topic": "wheatstone-bridge",
    "difficulty": "medium",
    "solution": "<p>Given all resistances have same resistance R.</p>\n<p>Now, we can redraw the circuit as below</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l3hevh7q/bee31c2a-f73f-4182-84a3-d00f539f63a2/c252f860-d9dd-11ec-8ea5-5be6b5e3368b/file-1l3hevh7r.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l3hevh7q/bee31c2a-f73f-4182-84a3-d00f539f63a2/c252f860-d9dd-11ec-8ea5-5be6b5e3368b/file-1l3hevh7r.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2021 (Online) 26th February Morning Shift Physics - Current Electricity Question 238 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>Let resistances be R<sub>1</sub>, R<sub>2</sub>, R<sub>3</sub> and R<sub>4</sub>.</p>\n<p>$$\\because$$ $${{{R_1}} \\over {{R_3}}} = {{{R_2}} \\over {{R_4}}}$$</p>\n<p>So, circuit will behave as a Wheatstone bridge and no current will flow through middle resistor.</p>\n<p>$$\\therefore$$ $${R_{eq}} = {{({R_1} + {R_2})({R_3} + {R_4})} \\over {({R_1} + {R_2}) + ({R_3} + {R_4})}}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = {{(R + R)(R + R)} \\over {(R + R) + (R + R)}}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = R$$</p>",
    "section": "A",
    "type": "SCQ"
  },
  {
