    "subject": "Physics",
    "topic": "wheatstone-bridge",
    "difficulty": "medium",
    "solution": "Let i<sub>1</sub> and i<sub>2</sub> be the currents as shown in the figure.<br><br> <img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1ky4imiet/765770d6-1a05-49c9-a335-8558d5a308af/28258560-6fc9-11ec-8887-d75613c1bf3a/file-1ky4imieu.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1ky4imiet/765770d6-1a05-49c9-a335-8558d5a308af/28258560-6fc9-11ec-8887-d75613c1bf3a/file-1ky4imieu.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;max-height: 60vh\" alt=\"JEE Advanced 2014 Paper 1 Offline Physics - Current Electricity Question 24 English Explanation\"> <br>Apply Kirchhoff's law in the loop ABCDA and CEFDC to get<br><br>$${i_1}{R_1} + ({i_1} - {i_2}){R_2} = {V_1}$$ ..... (1)<br><br>$${i_2}{R_3} - ({i_1} - {i_2}){R_2} = {V_2}$$ ...... (2)<br><br>Multiply equation (1) by R<sub>3</sub> and (2) by R<sub>1</sub> and then subtract to get the current through R<sub>2</sub> as<br><br>$$({i_1} - {i_2}) = {{{V_1}{R_3} - {V_2}{R_1}} \\over {{R_1}{R_3} + {R_2}{R_3} - {R_1}{R_2}}}$$. <br><br>The current through R<sub>2</sub> becomes zero when V<sub>1</sub>R<sub>3</sub> = V<sub>2</sub>R<sub>1</sub>.",
